As a druid I must profess that I cackled with glee at your suggestions for the druid class.  I for one am of the mind that druids *are* very, very broken end-game.  I can do lots of stuff soloing duoing, trioing and grouping.  But end-game, I'm pretty useless.<br>
<br>
I think POTG should be raised to something like 1600 or so mana and the HP should be raised to give somewhere between 700 and 800.  This woul not challenge clerics  for their slot as the best HP buffers, but would actually make using POTG on many people viable (Since you aren't trading off as many HPs for mana regen).<br>
